<plot>An artistic interpretation of William Blake's poem: The Marriage of Heaven and Hell (1790-1793). Arguably Blakes most influential work, the poem has fascinated academics and theologians alike. Set within contemporary society, the film represents an attempt to show that sin is more than simply an issue of right or wrong - good and evil. The film is newsworthy as authorities across the UK are trying to veto lap dancing using new legislation passed by parliament and after an Italian lap dancer quit after twenty years in the industry to become a nun.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?074135</url></doc>
